    {
      "id": "d1ff86d6-f3ff-4093-a5f5-8c9c4d5ee349",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Example 2: Check if a string is a correct FUV student email",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "d1ff86d6-f3ff-4093-a5f5-8c9c4d5ee349"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3360d87f-f23b-4ca8-80b7-de87226cf87b",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "void check_FUV_email(String email){\r\n    int len = email.length();\r\n    String e_tail = email.substring((len-25));\r\n    if(e_tail.equals(\"@student.fulbright.edu.vn\")){\r\n        IO.print(\"YES\");\r\n    }\r\n    else{IO.print(\"NO\");}\r\n}\r\n\r\nString s =\"Khoi.Bui.123456@student.fulbright.edu.vn\";\r\ncheck_FUV_email(s);",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "id": "3360d87f-f23b-4ca8-80b7-de87226cf87b",
        "executionSummary": {
          "executionOrder": 46,
          "success": true
        }
      },
      "execution_count": 46,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "execute_result",
          "data": {
            "text/plain": "YES"
          },
          "metadata": {},
          "execution_count": 46
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "0a0e0e6d-992b-474b-a0da-c0323895c224",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Example 3: How to assign 9 students into 3 groups randomly?\n“200102”, “210206”, “210230”, “220221”, “220027”, “220050”, “220216”, “230248”, “230036”\n\nBelow is the code you can use to generate a random integer\n\nimport java.util.Random;\n…\n        Random rand = new Random();\n        int temp = rand.nextInt();\n…\n",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "0a0e0e6d-992b-474b-a0da-c0323895c224"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "bc5668d0-9226-406a-ae25-e538e9b2f35d",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "import java.util.Random;\r\n\r\nString[] students = {\r\n        \"200102\", \"210206\", \"210230\", \r\n        \"220221\", \"220027\", \"220050\", \r\n        \"220216\", \"230248\", \"230036\"\r\n};\r\n\r\n        Random rand = new Random();\r\nfor (int i = 0; i< students.length; i++){\r\n        int temp = rand.nextInt(students.length);\r\n        String stu = students[i];\r\n        students[i] = students[temp];\r\n        students[temp] = stu;\r\n};\r\n        IO.println(\r\n\r\n        int temp = rand.nextInt();",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
